<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[781,1374,284,706]" lastBlockId="34.[159,1374,712,3470]" pageId="34" pageNumber="92">
Taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bocage" authorityYear="1898" box="[980,1150,402,431]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="angolensis">L. angolensis</taxonomicName>
has been problematic. It was formerly included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1821" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Rousettus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rousettus</taxonomicName>
, subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1912" box="[985,1143,476,509]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Lissonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Lissonycteris</taxonomicName>
. Based on morphological and behavioral characteristics and molecular phylogenetic analyses, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1912" box="[782,939,594,627]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Lissonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Lissonycteris</taxonomicName>
belongs in the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lawrence &amp; Novick" authorityYear="1963" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Myonycterini">Myonycterini</taxonomicName>
; in fact, it might be congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matschie" authorityYear="1899" box="[782,931,673,706]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Myonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myonycteris</taxonomicName>
. Here, the single species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bocage" authorityYear="1898" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="angolensis">L. angolensis</taxonomicName>
is recognized pending further studies, but some authors have raised subspecies goliath and ruwenzorii to distinct species. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
